{"aid": "40047544", "title": "Highlighter: Tcl/Tk app for reading and annotating PDF documents", "url": "https://wiki.tcl-lang.org/page/Highlighter+2%2Ex", "domain": "tcl-lang.org", "votes": 2, "user": "blacksqr", "posted_at": "2024-04-16 01:35:56", "comments": 0, "source_title": "Highlighter 2.x", "source_text": "Highlighter 2.x\n\n## Highlighter 2.x\n\nABU 15-apr-2024 - Updated to version 2.0.1 (includes license.terms )\n\nHighlighter 2 is a fully redesigned evolution of Highlighter, a full app for\nreading and adding annotations to PDF documents.\n\nWith Highlighter 2 you can browse and annotate multiple documents at once.\nDocuments are organized in a znotebook and they can be detached as independent\nwindows so that you can look at, compare, and annotate two documents at the\nsame time.\n\nHere is a preview\n\n### Download\n\nHighlighter requires the new tclMuPdf-2.x package. Choose the one for your\nplatform and install the package as a subdirectory of one of the directories\ngiven by the auto_path variable (e.g. c:\\tcl\\lib)\n\n  * [L1 ] tclMuPDF 2.4 for Windows x64\n  * [L2 ] tclMuPDF 2.4 for Linux x64\n  * [L3 ] tclMuPDF 2.4 for MacOS\n  * [L4 ] tclMuPDF 2.4 multiplatform /Windows+Linux+MacOS\n\nThen download the Highligther app. Unzip it and install it under any\ndirectory.\n\n  * [L5 ] Highligther 2.0.1 (Apr-2024)\n\n### How to use it\n\nDouble click on .../Highlighter-2.0.1/main.tcl or launch it from a shell\n\n    \n    \n    wish ..../Highlighter-2.0.1/main.tcl\n\nor\n\n    \n    \n    wish .../Highlighter-2.0.1/main.tcl mydoc.pdf\n\nUpdated 2024-04-15 22:20:39\n\n", "frontpage": false}
